accessibility.text: The van comes with:
2 - 110v solar panels that are easily removed and then re-installed
2 AGM deep cycle marine batteries (for extended camping and off grid activities)
An Eco-Temp propane hot water shower, shower blind for said shower (door mounted and easy set up and storage for transport)
5 gallon propane tank
Water pump
30 gallon water tank
A good size sink
Full size (newish) comfy mattress – bought new for a cross country trip last summer (only camped a couple of weekends since)
12v mini fridge,
4 bike bicycle removable rear mounted rack,
Extra large roof cargo bin
Roof rack for tying solar panels down or for a roof deck (which I had up then removed after our road trip)
3000 watt power inverter and extension cords (we used a projector set up to watch movies against the side of the van when we camp)
3 speed dual directional roof fan to help keep the van cool
Tons of storage space
New rear tires, very newish front tires
image2.jpeg
Perfect Burner Van.
Designed and set up to hit the road camping on a moment’s notice.

2006 Ford E350 extended camper van - comes with an upgraded 10 cylinder engine for mountain terrain and to haul large loads (like your boat or burner trailer). The engine is a beast—it’s a V10 and can get up any hill and through any situation you can throw at it; it’s also in great shape with 130k miles on it. I made extensive upgrades to convert this van from your basic cargo van into a solid off grid camper.
